				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Never doing the Epic!<a name="5387"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 13 03 7:50 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well, PoP is out. Here I am, level 63, and NO EPIC. Do I care? Not really... I've never had it, guess I don't know what I'm missing. I've got both scales, I've got everything, in fact, except Trak, the WW Skull (easy) and Eldrig's guts (also easy). I've just never gotten around to it...
<br />

<br />
Okay, okay.. I know by now some of you are wanting to KICK MY a$ for being a putz and not going out and DOING it. But as I see it now, it doesn't really matter... I want to wield the whatchamadoohicky that drops from the Keeper of Sorrows in PoTorment, because it's 2.0 singing and easier to get than the abalone mask. Well, that stick is 1hb and takes a hand. I want a decent weapon in the other, (Mr. Stick is only 15/20 or something, and bard melee suxx0rz) which doesn't really leave any room for Mr. Epic. Seeing as the epic is decent but not great, (other than 1.8 singing) I'm looking for other alternatives. For Epic equivalent or better: Use Range Drums (Denon's Drums of Declivity) for 1.8 percussion (Swapping in TDoK or WDotR for kiting anyway) and use Tear Shaped Ring for 1.8 stringed... What for brass? I dunno... Rizlona's call of flame is singing, not brass, and the haste from that song replaces the Vah Shir line, and the ervaj line sucks anyway... so brass isn't really important. If necessary there's getting the Blaring Horn of Fire or whatever it is from PoFire, but that would basically only be for lost comp and mana drain. (which is an excellent song) Then there's wind. There's actually a few one handers out there that are wind... One is Dirk of the Ravaging Wind(s) and has a very nice picture equipped. There's also that Malarian Wingblade that comes from... CoD I think... I think that's wind.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, I want to know what you guys think, post here, especially I want to get a listing of everything that counts as an instrument that does not have to go in your SEC slot. Thanks in Advance for your enlightened comments =)</span></td>
