			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Never doing the Epic!<a name="5465"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 16 03 8:58 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hmm! from where i sit, the bard epic is STILL the single best piece of bard equipment in the game, bar none.
<br />

<br />
I would not swap it for any of the above mentioned items for the following reasons:
<br />

<br />
1. The proc is primarily an attack rating buff, and as such is STILL an awesome buff for melees in your group.
<br />

<br />
2. You don't have to swap instruments to sing different songs.  In most small or large group situations there is just no way on God's green earth that you can twist four songs and swap instruments.  Lag is just too high.
<br />

<br />
3. No matter what aa you have and no matter what ungodly weapon you have, your melee damage SUXXORS!  Sorry to pick your ego balloon, hehe!  (I am gonna get lots of flames on this one, hehe! )  Nevertheless, after carefully examining logs of guild raids and comparing my damage to the damage of a similarily equipped pally with similar lvls and aa, I find myself as a bard hard pressed to do half the damage of a pally!  Sad but true!   Before you flame me on this, turn on others damage spam at the next raid you attend and log the spam and parse it.
<br />

<br />
4.  Your songs are far too powerful not to be maximized.  The damage shield alone from warsong of zek and psalm of veeshan with epic bonuses will more than make up for whatever percieved loss of melee damage you do for using an &quot;inferior&quot; weapon in your off hand.  Add in the extra heals from winds of marr on a thirty person raid against an ae casting mob?  Now try mezzing three even conning adds at once without an instrument!
<br />

<br />
5.  At high lvls, the increased stat caps mean that stats rule.  Even now its hard to find a weapon with the stat bonuses of the epic, let alone its other advantages.
<br />

<br />
Bards are complex, subtle, and very powerful characters to play.  If all you wanna do with your bard is run around in small circles endlessly chant kiting low blue mobs, fine, forget the epic.  But in group or large raid situations where the group  is hard pressed, fighting to the edge of their abilities, a bard with epic is easily worth more than two bard without.  I have been a bard without epic and a bard with epic, hehe, with is light years better!</span></td>
