				<td colspan="2"><span>Here is a nice similiar little post on the other eqdiva site that I thought I would share.
<br />

<br />
http://pub142.ezboard.com/feqdivabardsofeverquestfrm67.showMessage?topicID=624.topic
<br />

<br />
Samalander, congrats.  It seems you've reached a point in the game that aquiring such high end items is childs play.
<br />

<br />
Having said that, let me take a second and address a few of Samalanders points, not for him, but for others.   
<br />

<br />
We have on one hand (either hand) your epic.  Its simple,  great stats and resists, hp's, and acts as ever instument decent damage/delay, and a proc that helps out your entire group.  
<br />

<br />
On the other hand we have items that have instrument/singing mods.  If you look at many of those items you will see that there are better and cheaper alternatives to those slots or that the item is absurdly hard to get and most of them no drop.  If they are droppable, expect to pay through the nose for them.
<br />

<br />
Lets take the tear shaped ring for example, 1.8 singing mod, same as your epic, and 7 ac, 10 dex, 10 cha.  There are better alternatives to the stats on this ring out there.  The best thing it has going for it is the singing mod.  Lets look at some of those other replacements.    Another example, Dennons drum.  NO DROP, Vex Thal.  
<br />

<br />
Other Similiar high end instrument drops are either absurdely hard to get and also many are no drop.  
<br />

<br />
Why would you not want to sing Warsong of zek?  Or harmony of sound?  or requium of time? and gain the full benefit from them?
<br />

<br />
How many poeple are going to be wielding a rune stamped blade?  Or the rythem of Xegony?
<br />

<br />
One bard on a raid situation with epic though is quite defitinely better than one bard on a raid who doesnt have it, especially with a primarry hand drum.
<br />

<br />
Do your fellow bards a favor, when you sell your scales, try not to &quot;maximize&quot; your profit so much.
<br />

<br />
Baelwyn Laureatus.
<br />
64 bard.  Mith marr.</span></td>
