				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Never doing the Epic!<a name="5908"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 1 03 6:24 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Is the offhand weapon / instrument you are using right now better than the epic?
<br />

<br />
Will getting the three pieces you still need to get for your epic take longer than getting an RSB?
<br />

<br />
If both your answers to those questions are &quot;yes,&quot; then by all means forego your epic.  Give your scales to some unsuspecting Bard who just helped kill Naggy/Vox but a scale didn't drop, or give them to the Bards you rolled against and beat when they dropped.
<br />

<br />
But if your answers are &quot;no,&quot; then your reasons for not getting your epic are shaky at best.
<br />

<br />
But of course, it all boils down to the simple fact that it's your character.  Do whatever you want.
<br />
